+### iMessage
+
+iMessage ingestion requires macOS, `imsg` v0.13 or newer, and at least one
+explicit scope in `~/.openwiki/connectors/imessage/config.json`:
+
+```json
+{
+  "enabled": true,
+  "chatIds": [123],
+  "participants": ["person@example.com"],
+  "windowHours": 24,
+  "maxMessagesPerChat": 500
+}
+```
+
+`chatIds` contains positive numeric IDs from
+`imsg chats --limit 100 --json`. `participants` is an advanced,
+case-insensitive scope. When both fields are present, a chat must satisfy both
+(AND), so no conversation is selected implicitly. `windowHours` is bounded to
+1–168 and defaults to 24; `maxMessagesPerChat` is bounded to 1–5000 and
+defaults to 500. Run a configured source with:
+
+```sh
+OPENWIKI_WIKI_DIR=/absolute/path/to/wiki openwiki ingest imessage --print
+```
+
+If downtime exceeds 168 hours, ingestion fails closed rather than silently
+dropping messages. To deliberately accept the older gap, set `windowHours` to
+168, move `~/.openwiki/connectors/imessage/state.json` aside, and rerun. This
+recovers the most recent 168 hours and starts a new cursor.
+
+The connector keeps an exclusive Messages rowid cursor per chat and
+deduplicates by stable message GUID. It writes allowlisted normalized JSON only
+under `~/.openwiki/connectors/imessage/raw/<runId>/`; attachment binaries,
+absolute paths, contact-resolved names, routing diagnostics, read state,
+previews, polls, and reactions are not copied. Attachment entries contain
+metadata only. Connector directories are mode `0700`, files are mode `0600`,
+and every connector directory has `*\n!.gitignore\n`; raw messages never belong
+in the wiki or Git. Only compact synthesized pages are written under
+`OPENWIKI_WIKI_DIR`.
+
+Manual ingestion needs Full Disk Access for the terminal or parent process
+running OpenWiki. Contacts access is optional; Automation, SIP changes, and
+Messages send permissions are not required. Under launchd, macOS attributes
+Full Disk Access to the responsible interpreter, not necessarily to a script
+listed first in `ProgramArguments`. Inspect both before granting access:
+
+```sh
+launcher=$(/usr/libexec/PlistBuddy -c 'Print :ProgramArguments:0' \
+  ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.openwiki.ingestion.plist)
+printf '%s\n' "$launcher"
+/usr/bin/head -n 1 "$launcher"
+launchctl kickstart -k "gui/$(id -u)/com.openwiki.ingestion"
+```
+
+If the first line starts with `#!`, grant Full Disk Access to the executable
+between `#!` and its arguments, then require the `launchctl kickstart` smoke to
+succeed.
+
+To remove iMessage ingestion, run `openwiki cron delete imessage`, remove every
+iMessage entry from `sourceInstances` and legacy `sources.imessage` in
+`~/.openwiki/onboarding.json`, then review and delete
+`~/.openwiki/connectors/imessage/`. Review synthesized wiki pages separately;
+preserving or deleting them is an independent choice.
+
